## Summary

Fixes #5116.

Virtual interface member triggers unconditionally set a flag on every write
to a VIF-accessible interface member, regardless of whether the value actually
changed. This causes combinational convergence loops to run indefinitely,
producing a `DIDNOTCONVERGE` error. The issue was re-exposed by #6613, which
correctly connected member triggers to the trigger vector but retained the
unconditional write-flag mechanism.

This patch replaces the write-site flag mechanism with value-change comparison
at trigger evaluation time: `trigger = (current != prev); prev = current`.
Triggers now only fire when a member value actually changes, matching the
semantics of the existing `SenExprBuilder` infrastructure for regular triggers.

Also addresses the scenario reported in #6175. The gap was also encountered
while running CVV on Verilator (openhwgroup/core-v-verif#2724).

## Reproducer

```systemverilog
interface INTF();
    logic [7:0] data;
endinterface

class Writer;
    virtual INTF vif;
    function new(virtual INTF vif);
        this.vif = vif;
    endfunction
    task write_data(logic [7:0] d);
        vif.data = d;
    endtask
endclass

module t();
    logic [7:0] data;
    INTF intf_read();
    INTF intf_write();
    assign intf_read.data = data;
    assign data = intf_write.data;
    virtual INTF vif_read, vif_write;
    Writer writer;

    initial begin
        vif_write = intf_write;
        vif_read  = intf_read;
        vif_write.data = 8'hA5;
        #1ns;
        writer = new(vif_write);
        #1ns;
        writer.write_data(8'hB7);
        #1ns;
        if (vif_read.data !== 8'hB7) $stop;
        $write("*-* All Finished *-*\n");
        $finish;
    end
endmodule
```

On master (test is skipped by #6613; un-skipping and running produces):
```
%Error-DIDNOTCONVERGE: t.sv:19: NBA region did not converge after '--converge-limit' of 10000 tries
```

## Changes

- `V3SchedVirtIface.cpp`: Removed write-site `AstExprStmt` flag wrapping. Now
  collects all interface instance `AstVarScope` nodes with `sensIfacep()` set,
  grouped by `(AstIface*, AstVar*)`. Also extended `writesToVirtIface()` to
  cover `sensIfacep()` variables for `AlwaysPost` lifetime optimization.
- `V3SchedTrigger.cpp`: Added `TriggerKit::addValueChangeTriggerAssignment()`
  which creates per-instance prev variables, compares `inst != prev` (with
  `UNPACKED_NEQ` for unpacked arrays), ORs results into a single extra trigger
  bit, and updates prev after comparison. Skips non-comparable types (event,
  string, chandle) to avoid C++ compile errors on e.g. `VlEvent != VlEvent`.
- `V3Sched.h`: Changed `VirtIfaceTriggers` to store `MemberTriggerInfo`
  (vector of instance `AstVarScope*`) instead of flag `AstVarScope*`. Made
  `IfaceMember::operator<` deterministic (compare by name, not pointer).
- `V3Sched.cpp`: Updated `addVirtIfaceTriggerAssignments()` signature and
  both call sites (ICO and ACT) to pass `netlistp` and `initFuncp`.

## Test

- Unskipped `test_regress/t/t_virtual_interface_member_trigger.{v,py}` -- was
  marked broken by #6613. Added `--timing` flag to driver.
- Unskipped `test_regress/t/t_virtual_interface_member_trigger_real.{v,py}` --
  was marked broken by #6613. Added `--timing` flag to driver.

